  </div>
</div>
<p>
  Currently the UK has a money package on offer to those asylum seekers (even refused asylum seekers) to go home - there are few takers. Some of the migrants at Calais will have paid out £££thousands to their traffickers to get them where they are. - appears money isn’t their problem. Why should the UK taxpayer pay to send migrants home from France. IF France and the UK are both answerable to EU asylum and immigration laws, why does France accuse the UK of creating the Calais migrant build-up due to the pull of the UK’s generous asylum and immigration package - is France giving less than they should or is the UK giving more than they should.
</p></p>
